				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ E^{\rm corrected}_{\rm T} = E^{\rm uncorrected}_{\rm T} - \mathcal{O}(\eta, N_{\mathrm{PV}} , \tau_{\mathrm{bunch}} ), $$\end{document} where \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\mathcal{O}(\eta, N_{\mathrm{PV}} , \tau_{\mathrm{bunch}} )$\end{document} corrects for the jet offset due to pile-up.

Figure 5 depicts the distribution of the constituent tower multiplicity for jets based on towers with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
