After the jets in the nominal jet Monte Carlo simulation sample are calibrated (see Sect. 8), the jet energy and pT response still show slight deviations from unity at low pT. This so-called “non-closure” refers to a failed consistency test when the calibration is applied to the same sample from which it is derived. This can be seen in Fig. 11, showing the jet response for pT and energy as a function of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
