The systematic uncertainty due to the non-closure of the nominal JES calibration is taken as the larger deviation of the response in either energy or pT from unity. In the barrel region (0.3≤|η|<0.8) this contribution amounts to about 2 % at low \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
