				\begin{document}$\Delta\phi({\rm j_{1}},{\rm j_{2}})$\end{document} is the azimuthal angle between the two leading jets.

The lowest \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$p_{\mathrm{T}} ^{\mathrm{avg}}$\end{document}-bins are likely to suffer from biases. At very low \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
