				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\delta(\mathcal{O}^{\text{tower-based}})=100~ \mathrm{MeV} $\end{document} per vertex.20 The resulting total uncertainty is a factor of five smaller than the bias attributable to pile-up (≈500 MeV per vertex) even with this conservative systematic uncertainty estimation.

