				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathcal{R} ^{\gamma} \vec{p}_{\rm T}^{\gamma} + \mathcal{R} ^{\mathrm{jet}} \vec{p}_{\rm T}^{\rm jet} = - \vec{E}_{\mathrm{T}}^{\mathrm{miss}} , $$\end{document} where \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\mathcal{R} _{\gamma}$\end{document} is the calorimeter response to photons. Since the calorimeter is well calibrated for photons, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
