Jet rapidity acceptance: The analysis uses only jets with |y|<2.8 to have a smaller jet energy scale uncertainty on the recoil system. This selection, however, could cause an additional systematic uncertainty, if the fraction of jets produced outside the rapidity range differs in the data and Monte Carlo simulation. This effect is evaluated by studying MJB (calculated as usual from only jets with |y|<2.8) for events with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
