				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\sum E_{\rm T}$\end{document}) summed over all jets with 2.8≤|y|<4.5, in the data and Monte Carlo simulation. The agreement between the data and Monte Carlo simulation is satisfactory, and MJB is stable over the entire \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\sum E_{\rm T}$\end{document} range with the largest deviations up to 3 % at relatively high \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
