				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$p_{\mathrm{T}} ^{\mathrm{jet}} >20~ \mathrm{GeV} $\end{document} and |y|<2.8 calibrated with the GCW+JES scheme are used. Monte Carlo simulation distributions are normalised to the number of cells in data distributions. The ratio of data to Monte Carlo simulation is shown in the lower part of each figure. Only statistical uncertainties are shown

Figure 54 shows the distributions of the cluster isolation variable for all topo-clusters in calibrated jets with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
