				\begin{document}$p_{\mathrm{T}} ^{\mathrm{jet}} = 260~ \mathrm{GeV} $\end{document}. These results are compatible within the statistical uncertainty with the uncertainty evaluated using inclusive jet events (see Sect. 12.1.3).

The calorimeter jet response uncertainties for b-jets is evaluated using single hadron response measurements in samples of inclusive jet and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
