				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$b\bar{b}$\end{document} dijet events. The JES uncertainty arising from the modelling of the b-quark production mechanism and the b-quark fragmentation can be determined from systematic variations of the Monte Carlo simulation.

Finally, the calorimeter \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
