The jet energy scale (JES) and its systematic uncertainty for various jet calibration schemes are determined for jets measured with the ATLAS detector in the 2010 data set corresponding to an integrated luminosity of 38 pb−1. Jets produced in proton-proton collisions at the LHC with a centre-of-mass energy of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
